  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And this was-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we were also, I forgot-- would like to mention, we were also in-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] involved in, in having-- getting agents in every place in order to get all the information pertaining to that-- to that vicinity.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Now, it was in Lithuania-- for the short time that we had taken many of Lithuanians prisoners, especially those-- they used to call them the, the green ones because they used to wear a green uniform.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they were-- they were the ones that-- they were trying to sabotage the Russians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they were the ones that mostly killed, killed the Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I had, really, a great pleasure in, in the-- investigating some of them and translating.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And, of course, we were not able to kill them at that time because that was a, a, a general order from the High Command.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "But those, those people have been-- wound up in prisons.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And I'm sure they were-- they rotted in the prisons in the-- deep in, in Russia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Then I mentioned to you about the front in-- with, with Japan.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And I found out-- by coincidence I found out, that the whole regiment-- not only ours, there were a few regiment-- ours was one of the regiment that was transferred completely, fully to the Kurilian Islands, which is in the vicinity of Japan.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "I was the only one that this colonel gave me a transfer to the front to Germany-- to Zhukov's front.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And this transfer was very, very, very much valid.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And, and it really changed my, my life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Because all those who went to the Japanese front ultimately wound up in, in Russia-- somewhere in Russia or in Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
